
<REFENTRY id="passwd">
<REFMETA><REFENTRYTITLE>passwd</REFENTRYTITLE></REFMETA>

<REFNAMEDIV>
<REFNAME>passwd</REFNAME>

<REFPURPOSE>
change user password
</REFPURPOSE>

</REFNAMEDIV>

<REFSYNOPSISDIV>
<SYNOPSIS>
passwd [-g] [-r|R] group
passwd [-x max] [-n min] [-w warn] [-i inact] name
passwd {-l|-u} name
</SYNOPSIS>
</REFSYNOPSISDIV>

<REFSECT1>
<TITLE>Description</TITLE>
<PARA>
passwd changes passwords for user and group accounts.  A normal user
may only change the password for their own account, the super user may
change the password for any account.  The administrator of a group may
change the password for the group. passwd also changes password expiry
dates and intervals.
</PARA>
</REFSECT1>

<REFSECT1>
<title>Options</title>
<variablelist>

<varlistentry>
<term>-g</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Change the password for the named group.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>-r</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Used in conjunction with the -g option to remove
the current password from the named group.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>-R</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Used in conjunction with the -g option to restrict the named group for
all users.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>-x max</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Set the maximum number of days a password remains valid.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>-n min</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Set the minimum number of days before a password may be changed.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>-w warn</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Set the number of days warning the user will receive before
their password will expire.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>-i inactive</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Disable an account after the password has been expired for the given
number of days.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>-l</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Disable an account by changing the password to a value which
matches no possible encrypted value.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>-u</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Re-enables an account by changing the password back
to its previous value.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>
</REFSECT1>

</REFENTRY>
